The paper deals with Quality of Service (QoS) in Mobile Ad Hoc Networks (MANETs), which is a subfield of computer networking and falls under the category of Network and Internet Architecture (cs.NI). The paper also proposes a scheduling and MAC protocol model, which involves algorithms and data structures, making it relevant to Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DS). The paper also involves the use of simulation tools and techniques to evaluate the proposed model, making it relevant to Information Theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the security aspects of the proposed model, making it relevant to Cryptography and Security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper proposes a model that involves the use of algorithms and protocols to manage and control the network, making it relevant to Systems and Control (cs.SY).
